{
  "stem": "14060.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So therefore, the Hungarians have excelled themselves already to, to deport people before the actually the Germans came in to occupy the country.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there is no question about the guilt and complicity in the deportation of the Hungarian Jewry.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was another point I'm just forgetting.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I only made a few words of notes, which I wanted to add there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- we were geographically in Schoppernau, literally a pan handle into Austria.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in 1941 when the Germans-- in April '41-- invaded Yugoslavia, I have personally watched how the German units on trucks, motorcycles, tanks were going through the main thoroughfare of the town towards down to Yugoslavia.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Today, that's a question of an hour and a half to maximum two hour journey.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe those days, it took a bit longer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And literally in no time, they overran us, you know, Yugoslavia and Greece.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in that year, in 1941 already and in '42, similarly, trains were coming with Yugoslavian Jews through our town, and also Greek Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I remember distinctly that I stood at the railway-- next to the railway station where you could see a clear picture of these wagons which are run on-- not wagon [INAUDIBLE] wagons, but how they were transported.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't know where to.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The story was that they're going to go to work camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And, and there is a place called-- just a moment-- [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I forget the name of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there were cards received in Hungary by people from family or whatnot who were, in fact, deported to some of the death camps.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Where the Germans made them write camp that we are fine, we arrived, and this and that and the other.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was a great deal of deception going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
